{"questionId":"22151612","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>OA</mi></mfenced></math> is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>AB</mi></mfenced></math>, find the area of the quadrilateral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OABC</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;into their equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>so at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>area of triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>area of quadrilateral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OABC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22151612","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that OA is perpendicular to AB, find the area of the quadrilateral OABC.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrd